						<summary>

						<p>Northern wall of the kitchen in the Agastyēśvara svāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged and undated inscription may be assigned to the 16th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. It registers the gift of land to several brahmanas (names mentioned) of different <hi rend="italic">gōtras.</hi></p>						

